  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nWhen running a beacon node with many validators (512) **10%** (4030 ms / 45000 ms) of total CPU time is spent in `getAttestationsByDataRoot` since it is hashing attestations over and over and dropping the result.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/0bddc7ac75a0fab0356d29ebce6ea14f94a96458/packages/lodestar/src/db/api/beacon/repositories/attestation.ts#L29-L38\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nIt should be something easy to optimize for example doing what the TODO says\r\n```\r\n//TODO: add secondary index slot => root => AttestationData\r\n```\r\n\r\n<!--A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen.-->\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\n\r\nRun the multiNodeSingleThread test with 128 validators per node and attach a profiler\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\n\r\nThis is a very special condition since 100% of the validators of the network are connected to the same node. So the node is doing the same getAttestationsByDataRoot checks over and over, which won't happen as much in a real network, when you run a fraction of total validators. However the pool of attestations is likely to be bigger and have a greater impact\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2021-03-23 10-24-37](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/112123870-017fc880-8bc2-11eb-8c92-7222e47aca87.png)\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2021-03-23 10-23-37](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/112123891-080e4000-8bc2-11eb-8b99-a447435f1fec.png)\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2021-03-23 10-24-09](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/112123901-0b093080-8bc2-11eb-9cf6-e7ba4cac3db3.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
